# i18n & routing

No next-intl. Language is the `/th` URL prefix (English has no prefix).

| Kind | English | Thai |
|------|---------|------|
| WP pages | `/about` via `[...slug]` | `/th/about` via same catch-all |
| Home | `page.js` → `/` | `/th` via `[...slug]` (slug `/`) |
| CPT detail | `news/[slug]`, etc. | Mirror under `th/news/[slug]`, etc. |

## Detection pattern (use everywhere)

```js
const parts = pathname.split('/').filter(Boolean);
const isTH = parts[0] === 'th';
const slug = isTH ? (parts.slice(1).join('/') || 'home') : (path || 'home');
```

## Content selection

- Thai page HTML: `page.translations[0]` (title/content) when `language === 'th'`
- Block ACF: pass `isTH` / `preferTranslation` into `GetPageWith*` so translated `editorBlocks` are used
- Assume `translations[0]` is Thai — do not invent language-code filtering unless the API already supports it

## When adding CPT routes

Duplicate the English route tree under `src/app/th/{cpt}/[slug]/page.js` and pass language into the domain fetcher (e.g. `getPostBySlug(slug, 'th')`).

## Header menus

Menu DB IDs are hardcoded in `lib/header.js` (EN vs TH). Layout prefetches both; `Header` picks by pathname — do not re-fetch when `isServerSide={true}`.
